A 33-year-old Limpopo teacher has been arrested for allegedly raping a 17-year-old girl in Makwakwaila, outside Tzaneen. Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says the suspect allegedly raped the girl after offering her a lift. Ngoepe says the police condemn the continuous acts of violence perpetrated against women and children. The rape was reported to the police who reacted swifly and and arrested the suspect. He will appear before the Bolobedu magistrates court on a charge of rape.